# Expense Insurance Claims Gross Due To Reserve Changes Amount

## identifier
de8502

## type
float

## definition
This is the value of insurance claims expense which is due to prior period reserve releases or strengthening. This item refers to movements in outstanding claims due to changes in the assumptions used to calculate outstanding claims in prior periods. It includes changes due to the impacts of movements in discount rates and changes in the probability of sufficiency.

This item is determined in accordance with the relevant Accounting Standards.

Insurance claims expense is calculated as the sum of paid claims and the movement in outstanding claims liability for the relevant period.

